    <h3>How to clear short</h3>
    <p>Follow the below steps to clear short.</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Reduce the DC supply voltage to value not exceeding the voltage of the line you are about to clear short.</li>
      <li>Reduce Amps to around 1amps or less.</li>
      <li>Connect negative of DC supply to Ground of the motherboard.</li>
      <li>Connect positive of DC supply shorted part.</li>
      <li>Turn on your DC supply and gentle search for any heating component.</li>
      <li>If you can't find heating component, keep increasing the amps and search for any heating component.</li>
    </ol>
    <P>Once you find any heating component, take the component out of the motherboard and check impedance again at your
      testing point.</P>
    <P>If impedance is good after taking out the component, replace it with good one and proceed by testing motherboard
      after replacing faulty component.</P>
    <p>If impedance is still bad, repeat the same process untill the short is clear.</p>  
